Matrix of R colors in index number order

Plot matrix of R colors, in index order, 25 per row. This example plots each row of rectangles one at a time.

Matrix of R colors in hue order

Plot matrix of R colors, in hue order, 25 per row. This example plots each rectangle one at a time.

R color chart

Create 7-page color chart showing rectangle blocks of color, along with index, color name, and RGB constants in hex and decimal.

Define string vector of RGB hex and decimal constants for given color as a string.

GetColorHexAndDecimal <- function(color)
{
  clr <- col2rgb(color)
  sprintf("#%02X%02X%02X   %3d %3d %3d",
          clr[1],clr[2],clr[3], clr[1],clr[2],clr[3])
}

Example:

GetColorHexAndDecimal("yellow")
## [1] "#FFFF00   255 255   0"

Prepare text vectors to be displayed, in addition to color names.

index <- paste(1:length(colors()))
HexAndDec <- unlist( lapply(colors(), GetColorHexAndDecimal) )

PerColumn <- 50
PerPage   <- 2*PerColumn

Plot a column of color rectangles at a time for each page.
